        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 10:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1015 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kenton, or 27 miles west of Boise City, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Black Mesa Park, Kenton, and Wheeless.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
